        <div id='title'>
            <h2>ESCTT Inc.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="paragraph">
            ESCTT has been setting the bar in providing superior, cutting-edge technological training and solutions to the construction industry since 1977.  Through our Canadian Construction Association/Gold Seal accredited Microsoft Project, Microsoft Excel and Social Networking seminars, we help construction associations, companies and individual contractors to execute best practices and enhanced productivity and performance. What’s more important than staying within budget and on schedule? It’s our mission to provide you with the analytical, planning and tracking tools required to manage your projects and keep you profitable!
        </p>
        <p class="paragraph">
            Microsoft Project training has been the cornerstone of our business for nearly two decades. Our presence within the construction education industry is second to none. Over the years, we have had the pleasure of offering our seminars, both on-site and in-class, to the Ottawa Construction Association, the Ontario Sewer and Watermain Construction Association, the Electrical Contractors Association of Ottawa, the Mechanical Contractors Association of Hamilton and numerous other associations and companies.
        </p>
        <p class="paragraph">
            It is now with great pride that we introduce our ground-breaking risk management software, RiskMP.  Our team of world class engineers has collaborated to create this sophisticated, revolutionary tool that will allow project managers to systematically and proactively assess and address risk and unknowns in projects large and small. Where Microsoft Project and Primavera leave off, RiskMP steps in. As with all of our construction training seminars, RiskMP - Risk Management is fully approved and accredited by the Canadian Construction Association / Gold Seal.  
        </p>
        <p class="paragraph">
            Never leave anything to chance again - RiskMP formalizes the risk management process, allowing you to effortlessly incorporate risk into all your projects. And that means fewer emergencies, fewer fires and fewer late nights – not to mention more streamlined projects and happier customers! 
        </p>
        <p class="paragraph">
            Stay on schedule and within budget with RiskMP. We’ll show you how.
        </p>
